    "body": "# Potential Layout\r\n\r\n- ## Introduction\r\n    - Proof-of-Stake\r\n    - Consensus Clients\r\n    - Ethereum Readings\r\n\r\n- ## Getting Started\r\n    - Installation\r\n        - Install from Source\r\n        - Using Docker\r\n    - Creating a JWT\r\n    - Block Exploration\r\n\r\n- ## Beacon Management\r\n    - Configuration\r\n        - Available Flags\r\n        - Using a Configuration File\r\n    - Connecting to Peers\r\n        - Firewall Management\r\n        - NAT\r\n        - ENR\r\n    - MEV and Builder Management\r\n    - Database\r\n    - Syncing\r\n        - Checkpoint Sync\r\n        - Optimistic Sync\r\n        - Historical Sync\r\n\r\n- ## Validator Management\r\n    - Configuration\r\n        - Available Flags\r\n        - Using a Configuration File\r\n        - Proposer Settings File\r\n    - Key Management\r\n        - Fee Recipient\r\n        - Key Recovery\r\n    - Withdrawals\r\n    - Multiple and Fall-Back Validation\r\n\r\n- ## Logging and Metrics\r\n- ## Light Client\r\n- ## Prover\r\n\r\n- ## API\r\n    - Making API calls\r\n    - Using the `debug` API\r\n\r\n- ## Troubleshooting\r\n    - Common Installation Issues\r\n    - Common Sync Issues\r\n    - Common Validation Issues\r\n    - Common Execution Layer Issues\r\n\r\n- ## Supporting Libraries\r\n    - `libp2p`\r\n    - `@chainsafe/libp2p-gossipsub`\r\n    - `@chainsafe/ssz`\r\n    - `@chainsafe/bls` and `@chainsafe/blst-ts`\r\n\r\n- ## Contribution\r\n    - Bug Reports\r\n    - Getting started\r\n    - Repo Architecture\r\n    - Testing\r\n        - Unit Tests\r\n        - Spec Tests\r\n        - e2e Tests\r\n        - Simulation Tests\r\n        - Performance Tests\r\n    - Submitting a PR\r\n\r\n- ## Advanced Topics\r\n    - Migrating from Other Clients\r\n    - Slashing Protection\r\n    - Setting up a Testnet\r\n    - Doppelganger Detection\r\n    - Weak Subjectivity\r\n",
